{"title":"Structured errors for reviewer UX","gitnotes":1,"type":"markdown","body":"Parser failures now carry machine-readable codes — useful if the Hub ever surfaces parse diagnostics.\n\n```\n[BAD_VERSION] unsupported gitnotes version\n[MISSING_TITLE] expected title key first\n```\n\n| Code | When |\n|------|------|\n| `UNEXPECTED_TOKEN` | input does not start with `{` |\n| `MISSING_TITLE` | title not first key |\n| `BAD_VERSION` | `gitnotes !== 1` |\n\n- [x] `formatError()` for logging\n- [x] Line/column plumbed from tokenizer tokens\n- [ ] Export codes in public API docs (commit 10)\n\n> **Non-breaking:** `ParseResult.error` stays a string for callers."}
